examples.en: He stamped out of the room.
He stamped his foot in anger.
Erika stamped her foot in vexation.
My mother stamped off down the stairs.
The woman at the desk stamped my passport.
That episode was stamped on / in my memory.
The horses stamped and pawed in their stables.
The horse snorted and stamped its hoof impatiently.
Bills of exchange must be written on stamped paper.
Mankind had stamped its approval upon certain actions.
The experience remained stamped on her memory for many years.
His army years had stamped him with an air of brisk authority.
Her success has stamped her as one of the country's top riders.
'I will not!' Bert yelled and stamped his foot (=because he was angry).
The students' suggestion must be stamped on before it becomes a threat.
Send a stamped, self-addressed envelope (=with your address on it so it can be sent back to you).
If you would like a copy of our fact sheet, please write in, enclosing a stamped addressed envelope.
